President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Michigan due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for Crisis Counseling for affected individuals in all areas of Michigan. Additionally, funding is available for emergency protective measures and direct Federal assistance for all areas impacted by COVID-19 in Michigan. James K. Joseph has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on assessments and requests from the State. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.